06/08/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police arrested a man wanted for war crimes against Croatian prisoners of war, media reported on Thursday (August 5th). 
Veritas documentation-information centre chief Savo Strbac said Dragomir Casic was detained on August 1st at the Serbian-Croatian border while trying to enter Croatia. 
Casic was allegedly involved in the illegal detention and inhuman treatment of several Croatian police officers in August 1991. 
(B92, Beta, Srna - 05/08/10)
